caption: The pork belly ban mhi and the chicken catsu and the wings are the greatest thing I have ever put in my mouth. Get them!! The service is awesome and everyone could not have been more accommodating and lovely. The back garden is the perfect place to enjoy a meal, especially this time of year. My favorite new restaurant, and I am picky!!

Bixi is a sweet find! Excellent cocktails, sexy cool vibe and fantastic plates of South Asian flavors. Wonderfully executed I must add. From the super friendly and knowledgeable Service to the just right spicy cocktail to the sublime coconut rice.A welcoming, new restaurant in Harlem. I recommend :Pale Rider cocktail, Short rib wontons, steam vegetable pot stickers  tandoori chicken, shaved hanger steak. tempura bananas with chocolate sauce and rum whipped cream!
Went with a bunch of friends for drinks and apps.  We had a great time, food was awesome, exotic and lots of great drinks to try.  I had a little to much fun...
Great new addition to the neighborhood! Delicious food and attentive service. 10/10 would recommend!
My favorite new spot, amazing food, must try, love the decor and excellent service.

Went to Bixi On Harlem’s famed restaurant row for date night with my wife and we were treated to a sensory and tastebud overload of exotic  flavors. The decor and ambience, the music, the cocktails and the food were all amazing, as was the service. We sat on the back terrace, which was surprisingly tranquil and cozy. Definitely recommend BiXi to anyone looking for a new foodie experience!
Such a great establishment!  From the ambiance to the food to the cocktails to the service.  Everything was amazing! Kudos to the team at BIXI.  I'll certainly be coming back!
Great food, great service, great atmosphere. Would 100% recommend to a friend and will definitely be back!

My wife and I stopped by for brunch this past Saturday and it was well worth it!  We ordered the Croque Madame and the Waffles with Tempura Bananas.  To compliment we ordered 2 Hullabaloo's off the cocktail menu.  I recommend this new Harlem hot spot  - Bixi - to everyone!

Bixi is a great new addition to the neighborhood. I love the short rib wontons, ban mhi, and ribs and especially the cocktails!  Staff and service is excellent. Music is great. It’s a fun place to go for a night out!
This place is AWESOME! The food is incredible, drinks are made with a lot of love and the ambiance is very cool. I highly recommend Bixi for a great dining experience or drinks with friends!
Bixi is a whole vibe and the food is delicious!  We loved the ambiance inside and the outdoor space. Definitely recommend you trying the Wontons and Wings while you’re there!

Had the 5 Spice Baby Back Ribs and it was absolutely mouthwatering. A sizable portion that is reasonably price. Great food and drinks coupled with great service, with the ambiance and decor to match. I think Bixi has become one of my favorite go-to places in Harlem. I will definitely go back again and again.

Food was amazing, lots of flavorful choices. Has a really good vibe and loved the decor. Staff is warm and welcoming. Truly a great addition to the neighborhood. BIXI has a back yard area that is soon to open and will be spectacular for the warm weather. Strongly recommend this place!

We have been to Bixi a number of times. The food is always on point, love the pork sandwich and the fried rice. Drinks are delicious, sake selection really strong and service is so friendly. Great addition to the neighborhood.

If you haven’t been to BIXI yet, add it to one of your MUST visit destinations in Harlem! The decor is breathtaking and transports you to an exotic place, the cocktails give classic ones an unexpected twist, and the tapas style menu gives you the opportunity to try everything! The pork belly Bahn mi, chicken katsu sliders, short rib wontons and 5 spice baby back ribs are DELICIOUS!

I've become a fixture at this gem of a restaurant located in Harlem. From the time you enter Bixi you are taken in by the ambience, and made to feel welcome by the staff.  The food is mouthwatering and my margaritas were perfect!  My favorites are ithe Udon Noodles, the Vegetarian Summer Rollls, and the grilled shrimp salad!!!  Treat yourself to a unique dining experience!!!
What a waste!

From its opening I have fallen in Love with this interesting clientele, exotic menu and personable vibe.  The decor reminds me of old school North African Morocco  and even now during our pandemic, the staff is warm and welcoming.  Got a date?  Make Bixi a destination in Harlem!

BIXI is the newest spot to be in Harlem! Serving small Pan Asian Fusion platters: from Pork Belly Bahn Mi, Udon Noodles, Baby Back Ribs, just to name a few, they have so much food to choose from. Aside from the food, the cocktails are on POINT!!! They have their own variations of Mezcal Margarita, Spicy-Chili Margarita, Negroni, Old Fashion, and a sweet Coconut, Mango Rum Punch!!! The people who work here are professionals and their service is pleasant and welcoming. So if you are a local or visiting Harlem, please give this place a shot because it’s definitely not something to miss out on!

Came here for Valentine’s brunch and it was perfect!! Staff were sweet and informative about all my questions. Creative and delicious cocktails, not just the standard old fashioned or gin & tonic you can make at home, but fun and different ingredients, my fav is Lucky Jim (hello yummy egg whites!). The food is also wonderful even though normally I’m not a big fusion food fan. In a hood full of chicken sandwiches, their chicken katsu on that home made bread really stands out. Already craving it again.Totally recommend this place. Thank me later.

The environment alone brings you in sits you down and gives you a foot massage. From the food to the drinks everything is A one the people are fantastic and the overall vibe is spectacular especially in these COVID times we live in.
Beautiful environment, Jo the waitress was extremely welcoming and the owner Kwame made the place feel comfortable. Will be my main spot for 2021. Mocktails and food are very tasty as well

Look out Harlem, Bixi has arrived! Wow. What a cool, hip place with amazing food and drinks. Absolutely LOVED the Udon, just a lovely bowl of flavor and the noodles were perfectly chewy but cooked. Just a well executed representation of a classic dish. And I just have to mention the Baby Back Ribs. My wife flipped out they were so good. Perfectly tender and tangy from that rockin' sauce. Just a burst of flavor. I could go on but you get the point. Ok I lied, the Hanger Steak was fantastic as well. Served perfectly cooked and I don't think I have better rice than that coconut rice. Ok that's it. I look forward to returning and introducing my friends and family to this lovely new establishment on FD BLVD in the very near future!

The environment of Bixi Harlem is a calming space to relax. They were brillant to set a lounge with the decorative cool vibe that reminded me of old jazz scenes back in the day in Harlem.  The colors of the walls, seats, tables and dimmed lights all celebrated the vibe of a laid back comfy space.  The drinks were fantastic of course, enough to keep them coming as you enjoyed the scenery.   The food had a flare of of taste from around the globe that blowed my mind wanting to sample everything on the menu.  With that said, I will most certainly be a returning customer.  Truly enjoyed the Short Ribs Fried Wontons - your mouth will melt with the spices and the Undon Noddles were a hit too.

Excellent food, service and ambiance!  The place is just beautiful and sexy. The staff are super friendly and thoughtful. The food is exotic yet strangely familiar and the whole place has a great neighborhood vibe while somehow transporting you away.  And the drink menu rocks!  Great addition to the block and a sure fire mainstay for years to come. Can’t wait to go back!
The quality of food is not that good, but very pricy comparing the quantity of food. It is too overcharged. It is cheapest restaurant.

Words don’t really do this place justice. From the moment you walk in, you feel like you’ve been transported to another world. Thailand, Vietnam, Laos, Cambodia, the sounds, the smells, the vibe, Jimi Hendrix, The Rolling Stones, Muddy Waters, the sophistication, the deep red lacquered walls, the high gloss black wainscoting, the antique gold fixtures, sleek graphite zinc bar, the food, the food, the food..... And the cocktails, which look like works of art whipped up by some magical being. This is Harlem’s new crown jewel.

Bixi is one of my favorite spots in Harlem.  I have gone to Bixi over 5 times in the last two weeks, and I never get tired of it!  Not only is it a great bar with awesome cocktails and a large assortment of spirits, but the music is always fantastic and the ambiance is very nice and chic.  However, the best aspects of Bixi are the amazing food and staff!  My favorite food items are the ribs, short rib wontons, and pork belly bahn mi sandwich.  Everything is very flavorful and unique!  For drinks, I recommend the tin tiger for sure!   The atmosphere is fun and the crowd here is always lively.  They even have a backyard with a fire pit that gives off a lot of warmth even during cold winter nights. I recommend this spot to anyone in Harlen...you won't find anything like it!  It's a true gem!! :)

Seriously, tandoori chicken is soooooooooooooooooooooo small for  14 dollars. Oh my god the salad is like 10 dollars and just lettuce with one slice of avocado, and with someone else hair in the salad. This place is really bad. Honestly, I wouldn't even give 1 star!!!! do not waste your money on here.
They have very expensive food, and its qualities are not so good. I regret paying.

I’ve been waiting for this place to open as soon as I saw the sign go up and it did not disappoint. The short rib wantons were a savory-crispy dream. We also got the crab corn cake and bahn mi - both great. Do yourself a flavor-favor and check this new Harlem joint out. Excited for there soon to come brunch menu.

Bixi just joined the neighborhood (sister restaurant to Lido) and i hope that it survives the pandemic because i just had such a memorable meal. i ordered the pork belly bahn mi which was absolutely delish! it had all the right components and perfect ratio—soft crusty bread, sweet and savory pork, creamy avocado, tamari mayonnaise, cilantro, etc. the dressing that came with the side salad is addictive. the staff were also very kind and inviting. i can't wait to visit again and try more items! cheers x
